1. Introduction¶

This is an analysis done for an e-commerce firm based in NY, USA. In their business model clothing is sold online and they also have an in-store setup where customers can come in and have one-to-one sessions/meetings with a personal stylist. Thereafter they can decide to go home and order either on a mobile app or website for the clothes they want. In one of their strategy sessions they are debating on which chanel to focus and put more resources based on projected revenue . They want to also understand customer loyalty and if it has any impact on their revenue. The data set has 1000 observations

4.2 Error Analysis¶

In [45]:
from sklearn import metrics
In [46]:
MAE=metrics.mean_absolute_error(y_test,predictions)
MSE=metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test,predictions)
MAPE=metrics.mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_test,predictions)
RMSE=np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test,predictions))
In [47]:

5. Conclusion¶

The model has a MAE of 7.2 and RMSE of 8.9. Spending is highly correlated with length of membership therefore it is not likely to see any increased revenue if it decides to focus on either the website or mobile app. Rather focus should be on customer retention and building customer loyalty.
